directions: In the cafe area. There are gender neutral ones, a disabled one, some for those who identify wholly or partially as men, and some for those who identify wholly or partially as women. They are pretty obvious when you enter the building with the cafe; and it is usually not very busy.

name: Third Root Community Health Center
directions: Bathroom is directly to the left when you enter our lobby. It is labeled with an All-Genders sign.
comment: Third Root is a small, cooperatively-owned business where the majority of staff identify as queer and the rest are queer friendly. On all of our intake forms we have space for people to self-identify their preferred gender pronoun, and we also have a regular Sunday evening queer and trans yoga class. All are welcome to stop in to use the bathroom and help themselves to water or just a place to sit.
